<section class="section">
    <div class="pull-quote">
        The mental strength and calmness I find through yoga carry into everything
        else -- the work, the shop, the mentoring, all of it.
    </div>
</section>

<section class="split split--reverse">
    <div class="split__text">
        <h2>Project Yellow Jacket</h2>
        <p>
            My Jeep -- a custom rock crawler built on a 2004 Wrangler -- is a long-term
            project I've been chipping away at for years. Suspension, axles, drivetrain,
            body, electronics: almost nothing on it is stock anymore. The build lives on
            <a href="https://www.pirate4x4.com/forum/jeep-hardcore-tech/808300-project-yellow-jacket.html">Pirate 4x4</a>,
            where I post updates when I remember to.
        </p>
        <p>
            I love the Jeep because it never lets me forget what a tolerance is. Code
            gives you a little latitude. Mechanical systems do not. A quarter-inch off
            is a new problem.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="split__media">
        <img src="/assets/images/life-jeep.jpg" alt="Project Yellow Jacket" width="1200" height="900">
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
    <div class="pull-quote">
